<TITLE> More committees formed to oversee free textbook distribution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 28 (bdnews24.com)After a central body to oversee the distribution of textbooks free of cost at primary and secondary levels, the government has formed similar committees at all districts and upazilas. The education ministry's website on Sunday said the committees have been formed following two separate government orders. Deputy commissioners head the district committees and UNOs the Upazila bodies with upazila and union Parishad chairmen as members. Earlier on June 14, the government formed a central committee, headed by Dhaka University professor Muhammad Akhtaruzzaman, to oversee the printing and distribution of textbooks. The committees came to check irregularities in printing and distribution of textbooks. bd
